        <exercise workspace="1in">
            <p>True or false: if <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> are <m>n \times n</m> matrices, then <m>(A + B)(A - B) = A^2 + B^2</m>.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><p>If an example exists, give a <m>2 \times 2</m> example where this is true.</p></li>
                <li><p>If an example exists, give a <m>2 \times 2</m> example where this is false.</p></li>
            </ul>
        </exercise>
